  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-04-19",
    "date": "2023-10-06T15:05:51Z",
    "text": "Small Business Payment for Performance Act of 2023\n\nThis bill allows a small business that is awarded a construction contract by a federal agency to request an equitable adjustment if the agency's contracting officer directs a change in the contract's performance without the agreement of the small business.\n\nThe agency must provide the small business with an interim partial payment to cover additional costs resulting from such a change, and the small business must pay a first tier subcontractor or supplier the portion of the partial payment that is attributable to additional costs incurred due to the change."
  },
